08/03/2005
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- The Associated Press quoted Prime Minister Ramush Haradinaj as saying Tuesday (8 March) that he has resigned and will travel to The Hague Wednesday to face war crimes charges.
"I am one of those accused," he said, implying that others have been charged with him.
Details of the indictment against Haradinaj have not been made public;
however, he has been under investigation by the court for his role in the 1998-1999 conflict in Kosovo.
(Beta, Reuters, CNN - 08/03/05)
